      "stem_html": "<p>Draw the structure of the compound that produced the following spectra. The infrared spectrum has strong bands at 1720 and 1738 cm<sup>–1</sup>.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbGNYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--5d0a943ce3121e9a70775763581509012c5e6952/OChem_21_EC_064.jpg\" alt=\"The proton N M R spectrum of a compound of molecular formula C 7 H 12 O 3 shows signals at 1.25 (triplet of integral 3), 2.2 (singlet of integral 3), 2.6 (triplet of integral 2), 2.75 (triplet of integral 2), and 4.15 (quartet of integral 2) p p m.\">\n",
